<section id="robustness">
  <h2>05. Robustness Analysis</h2>

  <p>Adversarial rules were injected into the knowledge graph to test the Brain's resilience against bad knowledge. Three scenarios were tested: <strong>conflicting</strong> (rules contradicting existing ones), <strong>obsolete</strong> (deprecated API/version references), and <strong>biased</strong> (technology-biased recommendations).</p>

  <div class="chart-container">
    <img src="data:image/png;base64,{{ charts.robustness_degradation }}" alt="Robustness chart" />
    <p class="chart-caption">Figure 6 — Quality under adversarial injection (left) and resilience scores (right).</p>
  </div>

  <h3>Scenario Details</h3>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Scenario</th>
        <th class="text-right">Injected</th>
        <th class="text-right">Contamination</th>
        <th class="text-right">Detection</th>
        <th class="text-right">NDCG Baseline</th>
        <th class="text-right">NDCG After</th>
        <th class="text-right">Degradation</th>
        <th class="text-right">Resilience</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for r in robustness_results %}
      <tr>
        <td><strong>{{ r.scenario | title }}</strong></td>
        <td class="mono text-right">{{ r.injected_count }}</td>
        <td class="mono text-right">{{ "%.1f%%" | format(r.contamination_rate * 100) }}</td>
        <td class="mono text-right">{{ "%.1f%%" | format(r.detection_rate * 100) }}</td>
        <td class="mono text-right">{{ "%.4f" | format(r.baseline_ndcg) }}</td>
        <td class="mono text-right">{{ "%.4f" | format(r.degraded_ndcg) }}</td>
        <td class="mono text-right">{{ "%+.2f%%" | format(r.degradation_pct * 100) }}</td>
        <td class="mono text-right"><strong>{{ "%.3f" | format(r.resilience_score) }}</strong></td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="findings">
    <h3>Interpretation</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contamination rate</strong>: Percentage of returned results that are adversarial. Lower is better.</li>
      <li><strong>Detection rate</strong>: Percentage of injected rules flagged or quarantined by the Brain. Higher is better.</li>
      <li><strong>Resilience score</strong>: Composite metric (0-1) combining contamination resistance, detection ability, and quality preservation.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
